Articles.Content:
Hello all,

KSP has just started crashing inexplicably as soon as I double-click it to start. It had been crashing frequently before, and after one crash I tried starting it again and it gave the "the game crashed" message almost instantly. I tried again, same thing. Happens when I launch from Steam and directly from the Kerbal Space Program folder. I thought it might be my mods, so I removed them. Still, the game crashed on startup. It doesn't even get to the loading screen, it just crashes. I just tried it in 32-bit, no mods, and it loaded fine so it seems to be a problem with 64-bit.

Modlist (started with them in Gamedata but the crash still occurs in stock):

Spoiler

Atmosphere Autopilot

Better Burn Time

Contract Configurator

Contract Packs (from Contract Configurator, I believe)

Landing Height Display

Distant Object Enhancement

DMagic Orbital Science

Environmental Visual Enhancements

Docking Port Sound Effects

Graphic Memory Monitor

HullCam VDS

Raster Prop Monitor

Kopernicus

Addon Version Checker

KSPRC

Modular Flight Integrator

Music Mute

Navball Up Default

Docking Port Alignment Indicator

Kerbal Planetary Base Systems

Planetshine

RCS Sounds

Real Plume

Scatterer

SETI Contracts (from Unmanned Before Manned, I believe)

Smokescreen

Snacks

Station Science

Texture Replacer

Alternate Resource Panel

Unmanned Before Manned

Ven Stock Revamp

Rover Wheel Sounds

Module Manager

These are all pretty much up to date and were working just fine.
